<chapter id="chapter.chapter2"><title/How to use the Distribtion Panel/

<p>Here we give a couple of examples of how the Distribution Panel can be used. We describe a program with a special property and then we show how it is possible to see that property in the Distribution Panel. 


<section><title/Unknown/

<p>In a client server application where the clients and the servers are involved in heavy comunication even the smallest RTT flucturations can totaly ruin the performance. We monitor the server and observes strange transients in the RTT graph. The transients seems to come with an even interval. An inteligent guess is that garbage collection at the clinents and the server causes inaccessablity and thus raises the RTT.

