<section><title/Connection Port/

<p>Inspekting the Exported entities frame on a disconnected Mozart emulator shows a port in the scroll window. This is the port that the connection mechanism uses and not a bug. It is allways present to enable the Connection module to run.

<Picture.Extern id="TicketPort.gif" to="TicketPort.gif" type=gif>
<section><title/Unexpected Exports /

<p>Unintential exportation of Modules is a common bug in Mozart programms. With help from the Exported frame one can see all the entities that are exported. 
<Picture.Extern id="UxpctExports.gif" to="UxpctExports.gif" type=gif>

<section><title/Mass importation of Variables/
 
<p>When doing syncrone distributed calls using Variables for passing the answer a lot of temporary variables are created. Binding all the extra variables creates a lot of protocoll action and implies a lot of messages. 

